</td></tr><tr><td class="quad" colspan="4"><hr></td></tr>

<tr><td class="quad" colspan="4" ><a href="https://paperplaces.co.uk/2017/02/08/revolution-russian-art-1917-1932/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/OldDairyWoman-Grigoriev-1917.jpg" align="left" ></a>Boris Grigoriev's painting 'Old Dairy Woman', painted in 1917, and on display at the <a href="https://www.royalacademy.org.uk/exhibition/revolution-russian-art" target="_blank">Royal Academy</a> in London until 17 April 2017, reminds us of the harsh realities of rural ageing in pre- and post-revolutionary Russia while highlighting resilience and stoicism in older age.
