<tr><td class="quad" colspan="4" ><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-39153771" target="_blank"><img src="/images/IWD.jpg" align="left" ></a>March 8th 2017 marked International Women's Day with an emphasis on women's education, including that of <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-39153771" target="_blank">older women</a>.&nbsp;<br>
The day also saw the publication of IES blogs</a> highlighting the problems faced by <a href="http://www.employment-studies.co.uk/news/women-work-and-caring-unspoken-expectations-and-stifled-careers" target="_blank">women balancing career and caring responsibilities</a> and <a href="http://www.employment-studies.co.uk/news/older-women-work-doubly-disadvantaged" target="_blank">older women at work</a>. 
